We consider local minimizers of the functional \[ \sum_{i=1}^N \int
(|u_{x_i}|-\delta_i)^p_+\, dx+\int f\, u\, dx, \] where
$\delta_1,\dots,\delta_N\ge 0$ and $(\,\cdot\,)_+$ stands for the positive
part. Under suitable assumptions on $f$, we prove that local minimizers are
Lipschitz continuous functions if $N=2$ and $p\ge 2$, or if $N\ge 2$ and $p\ge
4$.